{"body":"\r\n","clean_title":"PE 205: Dice Game & PE 39: Integer Right Triangles","date":"Wed, 14 Apr 2010 23:55:27 +0300","euler_links":["https://projecteuler.net/problem=205","https://projecteuler.net/problem=39"],"euler_problems":"Problem 205 - Dice Game: Peter has nine 4-sided dice. Colin has six 6-sided dice. They roll and compare totals. What is the probability that Peter beats Colin? Answer to seven decimal places.\n\nProblem 39 - Integer Right Triangles: If p is the perimeter of a right angle triangle with integral sides, for which value of p <= 1000 is the number of solutions maximised?","explanation":"The first part of the code computes the number of ways to obtain various sums when rolling four 6-sided dice (Peter) and six 4-sided dice (Colin). It uses recursion to generate digits for the sums and stores the results in arrays. The probability of each outcome is then calculated to determine how likely Peter is to win given certain sums. The second part addresses a Project Euler problem where the code seeks to identify which perimeter value for a right-angled triangle with integer side lengths produces the maximum number of solutions, iterating through potential permutations of sides to find the optimal perimeter.","files":[{"binary":false,"content":"#include <stdio.h>\n\nvoid foo(int n,int k,int t,int* sum)\n{\n\t// n = digits range\n\t// k = current index position\n\tstatic char digits[100];\n\tint i,j;\n\n\tif (k==0)\n\t{\n\t\tj=0;\n\t\tfor (i=t; i>0; i--)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\t//putchar(digits[i]+48);\n\t\t\tj+=digits[i];\n\t\t}\n\t\tsum[j]++;\n\t\t//printf(\"   %d\\n\\n\",j);\n\t\t/*if (j==t*n)\n\t\t\tfor (i=1*t; i<=t*n; i++)\n\t\t\t{\n\t\t\t\tprintf(\"%5d %d\\n\",i,sum[i]);\n\t\t\t}*/\n\t}\n\telse\n\t{\n\t\tfor (i=1; i<=n; i++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tdigits[k]=i;\n\t\t\tfoo(n,k-1,t,sum);\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn;\n}\n\nvoid main()\n{\n\t// when peter will win? if colin sum is smaller.\n\n\t// prob(petersum=x wins) = prob(colinsum=1) +  prob(colinsum=2) + prob(colinsum=x-1)\n\t// prob(peter wins) = prob(petersum=x)*prob(petersum=x wins) for each x=1*9... 4*9\n\n\t// prob(petersum=x) = (1/(4^9))*number of times when petersum=x\n\t// prob(colinsum=x) = (1/(6^6))*number of times when colinsum=x\n\n\tstatic int petersum[4*9+1];\n\tstatic int colinsum[6*6+1];\n\n\tfoo(4,9,9,petersum);\n\tfoo(6,6,6,colinsum);\n\n\tdouble peterwins=0;\n\tdouble petersumxwins=0;\n\tunsigned long long z;\n\tint y=0;\n\n\tfor (int x=9; x<=36; x++)\n\t{\n\t\t// proccess of thinking:\n\t\t//peterwins + = prob(petersum=x)*prob(petersum=x wins) ==>\n\t\t//peterwins + = (1/(4^9))*number of times when petersum=x *prob(petersum=x wins) ==>\n\t\t//peterwins + = (1/(4^9))*petersum[x]*prob(petersum=x wins)\n\t\t// move out 1/4^9 from the sum\n\t\t//peterwins + = petersum[x]*prob(petersum=x wins) ==> in the end of the loop\n\n\t\t// calc prob(petersum=x wins):\n\n\t\t// prob(petersum=x wins) = prob(colinsum=1) +  prob(colinsum=2) + prob(colinsum=x-1)\n\t\t// prob(colinsum=x) = (1/(6^6))*number of times when colinsum=x\n\t\t// ==> prob(petersum=x wins) = (1/(6^6))*number of times when colinsum=1 +  (1/(6^6))*number of times when colinsum=2.. + prob(colinsum=x-1)\n\t\t// ==> prob(petersum=x wins) = (1/(6^6))* [ number of times when colinsum=1 + ... +number of times when colinsum=x-1]\n\t\t\n\t\t// can do it without loop\n\t\tfor (;y<x; y++)\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tpetersumxwins += colinsum[y];\n\t\t}\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\tpeterwins += petersum[x]*petersumxwins;\n\t}\n\tz = 262144; // 4^9\n\tpeterwins /= z;\n\n\tz = 46656;   //6^6\n\tpeterwins /= z;\n\n}","filename":"hila.cpp","language":"C++"},{"binary":false,"content":"\ufffd\ufffd/\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000*\u0000\n\u0000\n\u0000\n\u0000\n\u0000\t\u0000p\u0000r\u0000o\u0000j\u0000e\u0000c\u0000t\u0000e\u0000u\u0000l\u0000e\u0000r\u0000.\u0000n\u0000e\u0000t\u0000 \u0000-\u0000 \u0000p\u0000r\u0000o\u0000b\u0000l\u0000e\u0000m\u0000 \u00003\u00009\u0000:\u0000\n\u0000\n\u0000\n\u0000\n\u0000\t\u0000I\u0000f\u0000 \u0000p\u0000 \u0000i\u0000s\u0000 \u0000t\u0000h\u0000e\u0000 \u0000p\u0000e\u0000r\u0000i\u0000m\u0000e\u0000t\u0000e\u0000r\u0000 \u0000o\u0000f\u0000 \u0000a\u0000 \u0000r\u0000i\u0000g\u0000h\u0000t\u0000 \u0000a\u0000n\u0000g\u0000l\u0000e\u0000 \u0000t\u0000r\u0000i\u0000a\u0000n\u0000g\u0000l\u0000e\u0000 \u0000w\u0000i\u0000t\u0000h\u0000 \u0000i\u0000n\u0000t\u0000e\u0000g\u0000r\u0000a\u0000l\u0000 \u0000l\u0000e\u0000n\u0000g\u0000t\u0000h\u0000 \u0000s\u0000i\u0000d\u0000e\u0000s\u0000,\u0000\n\u0000\n\u0000\t\u0000{\u0000a\u0000,\u0000b\u0000,\u0000c\u0000}\u0000,\u0000 \u0000t\u0000h\u0000e\u0000r\u0000e\u0000 \u0000a\u0000r\u0000e\u0000 \u0000e\u0000x\u0000a\u0000c\u0000t\u0000l\u0000y\u0000 \u0000t\u0000h\u0000r\u0000e\u0000e\u0000 \u0000s\u0000o\u0000l\u0000u\u0000t\u0000i\u0000o\u0000n\u0000s\u0000 \u0000f\u0000o\u0000r\u0000 \u0000p\u0000 \u0000=\u0000 \u00001\u00002\u00000\u0000.\u0000\n\u0000\n\u0000\n\u0000\n\u0000\t\u0000{\u00002\u00000\u0000,\u00004\u00008\u0000,\u00005\u00002\u0000}\u0000,\u0000 \u0000{\u00002\u00004\u0000,\u00004\u00005\u0000,\u00005\u00001\u0000}\u0000,\u0000 \u0000{\u00003\u00000\u0000,\u00004\u00000\u0000,\u00005\u00000\u0000}\u0000\n\u0000\n\u0000\n\u0000\n\u0000\t\u0000F\u0000o\u0000r\u0000 \u0000w\u0000h\u0000i\u0000c\u0000h\u0000 \u0000v\u0000a\u0000l\u0000u\u0000e\u0000 \u0000o\u0000f\u0000 \u0000p\u0000 \u0000<\u0000=\u0000 \u00001\u00000\u00000\u0000